column14: I need extra time to do this lab due to the following time constraints and unique circumstances I had this week. On the first Saturday of the break, I went skiing and had to drive some legs. I was quite exhausted after so I just read the instructions to get familiar with the code I had to write. On Sunday, I had to prepare for a robotics class I was arranging. For background, I am the co-owner of Future Engineer Camp LLC (you can find it online by just searching the name). We run various camps such as robotics, Scratch, Java, and web development. We have grown to a considerable scale since the summer of 2019 and we have taught over 250 students, we have partnered with 5 businesses (after-school centers) totaling 7 locations, have a five-figure cash flow, and have a staff of over 20 teachers. As we were looking to expand our business this summer, we had arranged for a robotics camp to be run this week with a new partner as a trial class for around 10 students and hired 2 teachers for this. I had to dedicate a lot of time to find the teachers, ensure they were caught up on the curriculum, and make frequent visits to the class to make sure things were running smoothly. While this was happening we were drafting a summer contract with this business and another to finalize plans for classes to run this upcoming summer since we have to start recruiting new teachers and advertising my March. Additionally, we had to finish and file both the LLC tax forms (1065 and Schedule K-1s) and our self-employment personal income tax and Form 1040 after figuring out the numerous deductions and reimbursements. We also had to file/pay our franchise tax for fiscal 2020. As it is only me and a friend that are running this business, the arrangement of the robotics class, meetings with business partners, and tax filings took most of the day from Mon-Sun. I am also an investor and this week proved a critical time for a few stocks I am looking into. While this is certainly below priority of school work, I still had to do extensive research on a few picks such as RVLV, PLNHF, and CCL as I had to decide a purchase of these stocks this week. Since I am investing a relatively large amount for my age and this would contribute to a net worth goal of mine that would set me on a path to being financial stable despite college loans, these growth stocks were essential to building up my portfolio and I spent hours looking through news, 10Ks, 10Qs, analysis reports, etc. I hope you understand from the aforementioned activities that I did not have much time available for this CS project so I will be completing these by the resubmit date and I apologize for the lengthy write-up.
